            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.556</h2>
<p class="sub">A new interactive ride graph, a smarter Coach, and clearer iCloud syncing.</p>

<h3>New: explore your ride graph</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>Layer metrics together</b> — tap the chips to overlay up to four channels
  at once (power, heart rate, elevation, temperature, core body temp…) and see how
  they move against each other.</li>
  <li><b>Zoom in on any stretch</b> — drag across the graph to zoom into a section;
  the lines refit so it fills the view. Hit <b>Reset</b> to zoom back out.</li>
  <li><b>Scrub for exact numbers</b> — hover (Mac) or drag your finger (iPhone/iPad)
  along the graph and a readout shows every selected metric's value at that point.</li>
  <li><b>A linked route map</b> — tap <b>Show map</b> and a route strip appears with
  the graph. As you scrub, a dot rides along the route so you can see <i>where</i> you
  were; zoom a graph section and the map flies to it. You can also drag the map to
  zoom the graph — the two stay in sync both ways.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Coach: easier to read, and it remembers</h3>
<ul>
  <li>The Coach panel is now <b>expandable</b> and every reply has a <b>Copy</b>
  button, so longer answers are easy to read and reuse.</li>
  <li>Conversations are <b>saved</b> — reopen the history to pick up a past chat, and
  pin the ones you want to keep. They sync across your devices.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Clearer iCloud syncing</h3>
<ul>
  <li>A fresh install now shows an honest <b>"Setting up ChainLink"</b> screen with a
  real progress read-out instead of a wrong countdown, and your rides land as they
  arrive.</li>
  <li>A small <b>"Syncing with iCloud…"</b> note now appears whenever a background
  sync is running for more than a moment — so an occasional slowdown always has an
  explanation.</li>
  <li>New devices show your key numbers (fitness, totals, recent rides) almost
  immediately, instead of waiting for the whole library to download.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
