        <item>
            <title>0.3.542</title>
            <pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 05:46:14 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>542</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.3.542</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.542</h2>
<p class="sub">Makes the duplicate-bikes fix safe across all your devices.</p>

<h3>Fixed: duplicate bikes now settle the same way on every device</h3>
<ul>
  <li>0.3.540 and 0.3.541 taught ChainLink to merge bikes that iCloud had
  duplicated. But the two builds could pick a <b>different</b> surviving copy on
  your Mac than on your phone while iCloud was still downloading — and each
  device then removed the copy the other had kept. On a big sync that could
  leave you with fewer bikes than you started with. 0.3.542 fixes the rule so
  <b>every device always keeps the same original bike</b> (the oldest one), then
  moves all of its rides, parts and maintenance onto it. The merge can no longer
  disagree with itself across devices.</li>
  <li>Nothing to do — open the app once your iCloud download has finished and
  your bikes settle to the right set and stay there.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
