        <item>
            <title>0.3.541</title>
            <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 21:18:44 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>541</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.3.541</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.541</h2>
<p class="sub">Finishes the duplicate-bikes fix.</p>

<h3>Fixed: duplicate bikes (part 2)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>0.3.540 merged bikes that iCloud had mirror-copied, but not the ones that
  got <b>re-created</b> during a sync (e.g. Strava gear-matching built a fresh
  set before iCloud finished downloading your real bikes). Those twins share a
  name but not an internal id, so they slipped through. 0.3.541 now also merges
  duplicate bikes by <b>name + type</b> — a road bike and a gravel bike with the
  same name stay separate, but true duplicates collapse into one, with every
  ride re-parented. Open the app once your iCloud download has finished and it
  settles back to your real bikes.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
